The paper discusses techniques from computational geometry, combinatorics, and convex optimization to solve optimization problems involving non-convex functions. This suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper provides applications in computer vision (points-to-lines alignment) and augmented reality, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of coresets, which are a technique commonly used in numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
